    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom of the stems are turning this sickly yellow color but the top ones look okay. what's probably going on and how do i fix the soil?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on the bottom of your tomato plants, while the top ones are still green, is a classic sign of a nutrient deficiency, often related to nitrogen or potassium, or perhaps a watering issue. You can try to fix this by amending your soil with a balanced, slow-release organic fertilizer, or by giving them a liquid feed rich in nitrogen, which is what the lower leaves are usually crying out for. Remember, even the most robust tomato plant can get stressed if its soil is too dry or too soggy, so check the moisture level deep down in the pot or ground.",
